1) The following data sources have been used: Education and Training - 2008/09 (L05, U05 Final), 2009/10 (L05, U05 Final), 2010/11 (LR05 Final); Workplace Learning and Apprenticeships - 2008/09 (E13 Final), 2009/10 (E13 Final), 2010/11 (ER13 Final); Community Learning - 2008/09 (C05 Final, C04 Final), 2009/10 (C05 Final), 2010/11 (SL05 Final).

2) Participation volumes are rounded to the nearest ten except Grand Totals which are rounded to the nearest hundred; percentages are calculated based on pre-rounded data. '-' Indicates a base value of less than five or a percentage of less than 0.5%.

3) Success rates are calculated as the number of learning aims achieved divided by the number of starts, excluding any learners who transferred onto another qualification within the same organisation. Learners who withdrew within the first 6 weeks of the qualification are excluded. Percentages are rounded to the nearest one decimal place; percentages are calculated based on pre-rounded data.  '-' Indicates when the number of related cohorts is less than 30 or the number of achievers is under 5.

4) Full-year participation numbers are a count of the number of learners that participated at any point during the year. Learners included in different data collections, where this is different funding streams, will appear in more than one related table. Learners included in different data collections, where this relates to different years, will be counted against each year.

5) To allow for comparison between different data sources, tables use age as at 31 August of the academic year for all provision. These tables include learners aged 19 and over only, except the Apprenticeship tables which show all ages.
6) Age, ethnicity, gender and learners with learning difficulties and/or disabilities is based upon self-declaration by the learner.
7) For success rate methodology for 2010/11 please see the following paper:
8) 'Total BAME' is the sum of learners from a Black, Asian or Minority Ethnic group.
9) Provider Type is as recorded in the associated Academic Year.
10) Special Colleges include Agriculture and Horticulture Colleges;  Art, Design and Performing Arts Colleges and Specialist Designated Colleges.

11) Other Public Funded includes Central Government Department, Central Government NDPB, Public Corporations & Trading Funds, Local Education Authority (LEA), Social Services, Other Local Authority, Police Authority, Fire Authority, Local Authority Dept, Local Authority, NHS-English Foundation Trust, NHS-English Non Foundation Trust, NHS-Other Organisations, Independent school or college, UFI Directly Funded Hub, Dance and Drama School, External Institution, Higher Education Organisation, School Sixth Form (not college), Special learning needs establishment, Other Public Organisation, Charitable, Non-Charitable, Other Voluntary Organisation, LSC Region, Special College,Academies, External Institution, Institution funded by other Govt Dept, University Technology College.
